      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores how artificial intelligence is increasingly being used to monitor and control critical parameters in chemical processing environments, including temperature, pressure, and chemical reactions. As AI systems take on greater responsibility for managing these variables, it is essential for those working in the industry to understand the potential safety implications that can arise when things go wrong. We will examine real-world scenarios where AI-driven decisions could lead to hazardous outcomes, and consider how human oversight remains a vital safeguard in automated processes. The lesson is designed for beginners, so no prior knowledge of AI or chemical engineering is required, just a willingness to engage with the topic in a practical and safety-focused way. By the end, you will have a clearer understanding of both the benefits and the risks that come with integrating AI into chemical processing operations.",
